Ph.D. Advisor  Dr. Nancy  Boyd Lillie       BLB 385L       (940) 565-3158 Nancy.Boyd.Lillie@unt.edu   The Department of Management's objective for its Ph.D. program is to create and maintain a small, quality program where each student will find the opportunity to excel in the areas of teaching and research. To meet this objective, we have developed a curriculum that involves students in coursework on research methods and processes, teaching methodology, the study of scientific philosophies that form the foundation for scholarly research, statistical analyses, and in depth study of the management discipline. General Requirements By clicking on the following links, you will be taken to the Ph.D. advising site for more general information concerning the program requirements for the Ph.D. program in Business Administration.  Admission to the program Qualifying Exam Course Work  Dissertation Important Dates and Deadlines        Physical Address:              University of North Texas             College of Business             1307 West Highland Street             Denton, Texas             76201 Contact the College of Business    Mailing Address:        University of North Texas       College of Business       1155 Union Circle #311160       Denton, TX        76203-5017 Contact the College of Business    This Website:              © 2017 UNT College of Business             For issues or comments related to this website, please contact us.                    Disclaimer |            AA/EOE/ADA |            Privacy  |            Web Accessibility |            State of Texas Online |            Emergency Preparedness |            THECB Online Resume System      
